=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucygoth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cygoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/15/02 1:36:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1782.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> *</span><hr size=1> Perhaps your title should say 'Level 22 twink monk needs reassurance', or something like that. With the gear and pp you have for your level it won't matter a damn what you do, you can just walk all over yellows. My gear isn't half as good as yours at 24 (100% twink free on FV), and I can easily take most whites, but most yellows beat the snot out of me. Well, except casters - they go down like a presidential aide. Of couse, I play as a druid pet regularly, so I can take reds <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Well, at least I can stand there and swing at them until they die - that's almost the same thing, right?<br>Why not buy a fungi and silver chitin handwraps? They might make your life 'easier' (lol), but the fungi might be either too expensive or unavailable, depending on your server (on FV there isn't any no-drop, so I don't remember what is or isn't no-drop on other servers)  With the small change you could get nice wrists (bracers of erollisi? buy/MQ a Shuriken dispenser?), and shoulders (drolvarg, greyhopper, reinforced acrylia?). Your biggest problem will be finding enough yellows in one place so that you can kill continuously.<br>I would also be trying to get stamina over 100, especially if you end up with a 2HB, but even if you're using 1HB, the weapons are still heavy and fast enough to drain you quick. If you unequip your off-hand weapon for the first bubble of each level then your H2H will keep up - you could just put a PSU in it for the ac and stats if it makes you feel better (I don't bother), but there aren't many H2H weapons that compare with the available 1HB at low-mid levels. Good luck finding a fast, light 2HB to raise your skills with. I've been looking for a Bamboo Bo Staff since level 5, and I still haven't found one for sale at any price. Nearly every monk usable 2HB weighs 9-10 stone. Go figure. Someone suggested a shovel, but I'd like to survive the experience <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udakkin2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dakkin2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/15/02 2:14:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1782.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 22 monk needs help.  </span><hr size=1> Hi Hamirez<br><br>1Hbs tend to be better unless you have serious money to spend, because for what you can afford they do more damage without weighing you down enough to eat into your AC a little later on.<br><br>Since you have reasonable 1Hbs anyway, I'd be inclined to hang on to them, and maybe browse the Bazaar for a moderate 2Hb to skill up on with whatever money you have left after upgrading your armour.<br><br>SC handwraps would be nice provided you're on one of those servers where they're priced so you can swap them out for the FBSS with a little change on top; if it'll cost you 6K then I'd say you need the money for other things.<br><br>Most importantly, look for acrylia reinforced and spider fur armour for as many slots as you can afford (starting with the empty ones), to bump up your AC and stats.<br><br>Dak<br><br>PS  This is assuming you can find Acrylia reinforced or similar armour for around 1K a slot or so; prices vary a lot from server to server. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udakkin2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dakkin2</A> at: 8/15/02 4:12:34 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udeputygrima.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deputy Grima</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/15/02 5:20:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1782.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 22 monk needs help.  </span><hr size=1> Kill Zelniaks in Marus Seru, u should be fine.  Yellows are easy for non twinks at 25, but you should be ok at 23 or so. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=siward>Siward</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/15/02 10:53:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1782.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 22 monk needs help.  </span><hr size=1> Cygoth: he will not be able to &quot;walk all over yellows.&quot; i am 100% sure about this. he can kill one, but with substantial downtime until the next.<br><br>Also, you are suggesting for him to buy a fungi tunic?! on almost every server they are 30k+.<br><br>Stick with 1hbs until 45 my friend. make sure that you keep 2hb maxed in the mean time.  goranga spiked club and stave of sheilding still out damages IFS at 45ish, but IFS will beat them with epic. (pretty sure).  i recommend the GSC and SoS combo.  i recommend selling the FBSS, buying SCHW (silver chitin handwraps) and with whats left, go for HPs and AC.<br><br>good luck <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310367">siward turtlestomper</a><BR><table style="filter:glow(color=Blue, strength=1)"><font color="black" size=2><b>41 monk of quellious</b></font></table><b>order of infinite darkness</b><br>fennin ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucygoth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cygoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/16/02 12:59:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1782.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> *</span><hr size=1> On FV I commonly see items for under 100pp that are listed at 10K plus on EQPrices, so while I don't know the prices on other servers, I do know that the variance is huge. If he has a level 50+ lying around on the same server he could farm stuff for any cash that he needs, and you don't twink a monk like that and have 11k to spare if your main is a level 25 paladin <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>At 21ish I could easily 'walk over' yellow Aviak guards and be at full health with mend up for the next pop. However, at 24, yellow Tesch Mas Gnolls beat the snot out of me. Blue Griffxxx's have always torn me several new orifices <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  So I think it comes down to specific mobs, with old-world mobs being a good deal easier than their new world counterparts. When he fills out his empty slots his ac will be nearly 100 above what I had then, and his weapons and haste will give him almost double the damage output. If he can't walk over select old-world yellows one after the other in that gear then he must have accidentally equipped his GLS in his primary slot (I haven't done that since..erm....yesterday *blush*).<br>But then what do I know? I'm only of a similar level and doing similar things - I don't even have 'Grandpoobah' ahead of my name <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showNextMessage?topicID=1782.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1782.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.emailToFriend?topicID=1782.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.threadControl?topicID=1782.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1782.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1782.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br>